## Verification
- `sysID_wrapper.sh .../OD1A053_rpyChirp_PA60_sysid.yaml` → completes r/p/y; `config.json` + copied
  yaml in the rundir; `run.log` shows `[Roll] time slice 695-725 s -> N samples` etc.
- `figures/Time_Slices_Overview.png`: the three shaded windows sit on the three chirps (confirms the
  absolute-time assumption). Per-axis `*_Time_Domain_Data.png` spans only its window.
- `margins.txt` shows the per-axis slice; identification numbers differ from a full-series run.
- Back-compat: passing the `.ulg` directly still runs (full series, no slicing).
- Fast iteration: the `.mat` already exists beside the ulg; pointing `ulg_path` at it skips the
  ~1-min re-extraction.
